-- Marlins’ Fernandez Wins NL Rookie of Year Award Over Yasiel Puig
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2013-11-11T23:56:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-11/marlins-fernandez-wins-nl-rookie-of-year-award-over-yasiel-puig.html
Miami Marlins pitcher Jose Fernandez
was voted the National League Rookie of the Year over Los
Angeles Dodgers outfielder Yasiel Puig after both Cuban players
had breakout debut seasons in  Major League Baseball .  St. Louis Cardinals pitcher Shelby Miller was the third NL
rookie finalist in voting conducted by the Baseball Writers’
Association of America.  Tampa Bay outfielder Wil Myers was selected as the  American
League ’s top rookie, becoming the third Rays player in the last
six seasons to win the award. Myers finished ahead of Rays
pitcher Chris Archer and Detroit Tigers shortstop Jose Iglesias.  The rest of MLB’s top honors -- Most Valuable Player,
Manager of the Year and the Cy Young Award given to pitchers --
will be announced later this week.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
